# Cursor Rules Guide

## Rules Location

All rules are in `.cursor/rules/`:

```
.cursor/rules/
├── index.mdc           # Always applied - project overview
├── react-components.mdc # Component patterns
├── state-management.mdc # Zustand & TanStack Query
├── routing.mdc          # TanStack Router
├── styling.mdc          # Tailwind & shadcn/ui
├── api-data.mdc         # API & data fetching
├── testing.mdc          # Vitest & MSW
├── player.mdc           # Media player system
└── cursor-rules.mdc     # This file
```

## Rule Types

### Always Applied
Set `alwaysApply: true` - applies to every conversation:

```yaml
---
description: Project overview
alwaysApply: true
---
```

### Glob-Based
Set `globs:` pattern - applies when matching files are involved:

```yaml
---
description: Component patterns
globs: src/components/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---
```

### Manual Reference
Set `alwaysApply: false` without globs - agent decides when relevant.

## Creating New Rules

1. Create file in `.cursor/rules/` with `.mdc` extension
2. Use kebab-case naming: `my-new-rule.mdc`
3. Add frontmatter with description and applicability
4. Write clear, actionable content with code examples

## Frontmatter Structure

```yaml
---
description: Short description shown in rule list
globs: optional/path/**/*.ts,other/path/**/*.tsx
alwaysApply: false
---
```

- `description`: Required. Explains when/why to use the rule
- `globs`: Optional. Comma-separated glob patterns
- `alwaysApply`: Required. Boolean for automatic application
